article.headline: Old Dominion 62, Drexel 52
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Arnaud Dahi had 14 points and 17 rebounds to lead Old Dominion to a 62-52 win over Drexel on Thursday night. Drew Williamson and Valdas Vasylius added 14 points, and Brian Henderson scored 11 for the Monarchs (9-3 Colonial Athletic Association 16-7), who won their fourth straight. Old Dominion took control in the second half with a 12-2 run over a 4:14 span. Brian Henderson's jumper with 6:35 remaining capped the run and gave the Monarchs their biggest lead of the game at 52-39. Frank Elegar scored 16 points, Bashir Mason added 10 and Chaz Crawford finished with 13 rebounds for the Dragons (8-4, 16-6), who were slowed by poor shooting. Drexel shot just 27 percent from the field. The Monarchs scored the final four points of the first half and the first seven of the second to open a 38-27 lead with 16:37 left. The Dragons rallied, scoring eight straight points and moving within 40-37 with 11:40 remaining before the Monarchs pulled away.
